# Copy to `.env` or `.env.local` and restart `npm run dev` after changes.
#
# Local dev + remote backend (recommended): leave VITE_API_BASE_URL unset and set:
#   VITE_API_PROXY_TARGET=https://your-backend.onrender.com
# The browser only talks to the Vite dev server; Node proxies to the API (no browser CORS issues).
#
# Production / static hosting: set the API root explicitly:
#   VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://your-backend.onrender.com
#
# Local backend on port 8000: leave VITE_API_BASE_URL unset; either omit VITE_API_PROXY_TARGET or set
# VITE_API_PROXY_TARGET=http://localhost:8000
#
# Optional. Used for GET /api/visits/provider/{id} on the Visits list. Backend still returns visits with no provider_id.
# VITE_PROVIDER_ID=default
